description: Returns the detailed parameter list for a particular DB parameter group.

parameters.name: DBParameterGroupName
parameters.description: The name of a specific DB parameter group to return details for. Constraints: If supplied, must match the name of an existing DBParameterGroup.

parameters.name: Source
parameters.description: The parameter types to return. Default: All parameter types returned Valid Values: user | system | engine-default.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: A filter that specifies one or more DB parameters to describe. The only supported filter is parameter-name. The results list only includes information about the DB parameters with these names. (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a describe operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as IDs. The filters supported by a describe operation are documented with the describe operation. The following actions can be filtered: DescribeDBClusterBacktracks DescribeDBClusterEndpoints DescribeDBClusters DescribeDBInstances DescribeDBRecommendations DescribeDBShardGroups DescribePendingMaintenanceActions The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. One or more filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. (string) ---

parameters.name: MaxRecords
parameters.description: The maximum number of records to include in the response. If more records exist than the specified MaxRecords value, a pagination token called a marker is included in the response so that you can retrieve the remaining results. Default: 100 Constraints: Minimum 20, maximum 100.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: Provides a description of the parameter.

nested_items.name: Source
nested_items.description: The source of the parameter value.

nested_items.name: ApplyType
nested_items.description: Specifies the engine specific parameters type.

nested_items.name: DataType
nested_items.description: Specifies the valid data type for the parameter.

nested_items.name: AllowedValues
nested_items.description: Specifies the valid range of values for the parameter.

nested_items.name: IsModifiable
nested_items.description: Indicates whether ( true) or not ( false) the parameter can be modified. Some parameters have security or operational implications that prevent them from being changed.

nested_items.name: MinimumEngineVersion
nested_items.description: The earliest engine version to which the parameter can apply.

nested_items.name: ApplyMethod
nested_items.description: Indicates when to apply parameter updates.

nested_items.name: Marker
nested_items.description: An optional pagination token provided by a previous request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by MaxRecords.
